This project uses Vite with a base path configuration (`base: "/copivaga-landing/"` in `vite.config.ts`). When referencing any assets from the `public` folder (images, SVG files, etc.), you must use the `BASE_URL` constant from `@/lib/constants` to construct the correct path.

## Import BASE_URL

Always import BASE_URL from the centralized constants file:

```typescript
import { BASE_URL } from "@/lib/constants";
```

## Correct Usage:

```typescript
import { BASE_URL } from "@/lib/constants";

// In JSX:
<img src={`${BASE_URL}logo.svg`} alt="Logo" />
<img src={`${BASE_URL}images/example.png`} alt="Example" />
```

## Incorrect Usage:

```typescript
// ❌ DON'T define BASE_URL locally
const BASE_URL = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;

// ❌ DON'T use absolute paths starting with /
<img src="/logo.svg" alt="Logo" />
<img src="/images/example.png" alt="Example" />
```

